node.text:
This winter, taking out means more than staying in, as every order counts to support our amazing local restaurants and the people who continue to bring us delicious meals. Wherever you might be, this is a great time to step up and join the effort to save restaurants. 

We love seeing our great Napa Valley restaurant community come together and how people are rallying to make a difference, including ordering takeout meals. Here are some other ways to help out: 

✅ Buy a gift card or certificate to help restaurants maintain business, while they’re unable to safely open 
✅ Write a positive review on Google, Yelp, OpenTable or your preferred review platform 
✅ Promote information on restaurant openings, local offerings or reshare this video to your friends and family on social media 

Help spread the word — Tag your favorite restaurants in the comments below!

node.text:
With harmonious tannins, Caymus-Suisun Grand Durif (aka Petite Sirah) is opulent, luxuriously soft and totally enjoyable. The 2018 vintage is the fifth that Chuck Wagner has produced from grapes farmed in Suisun Valley. Located only a 30-minute drive southeast of Napa, this wine region has rich soils that are perfectly conducive to growing exceptional Petite Sirah.

Drink Grand Durif alongside your favorite steak cut to find a match made in heaven.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Caymus Vineyards on June 20, 2021. May be a black-and-white image of 2 people.

node.text:
"When my parents asked me, in 1972, to join them in founding Caymus Vineyards, I didn't hesitate. I knew that my father would be tireless in working in the vineyards in his family's tradition, but also open to new ideas and new directions, as long as he believed they would lead to better wine. This was true both in the short term and the long term. And in the wine business, the long term can be very, very long indeed." - Chuck Wagner.

While Charlie Wagner Sr. is no longer with us, his example lives on. To all the dads for what they've given us — thank you!
